This was a Great Movie. Anybody who loves football or sport should watch it.

The guy who played the Referee in the Movie(Last Football scene)Was my Math Teacher(he Not at Carson anymore, he Teaches/Coaches  in a different Town now) He is long Gone and no longer Teaches or Coaches at Carson. He was my Math Teacher in 11th Grade and is the Current Head Football Coach(in his fifth year now)at My High School in which I was one of the Managers of the team.
I liked this movie, cause it was shot in Carson City. Also cause my cousins, my brother & I were in it.
The quality, as well as the movie itself, is terrible.
Very disjointed and rambling. Bad acting and a worse story line.

I didn't make it past the first 20 minutes if that. Very fake and just not believable acting.
Did not like it at all.

How sloooooow can this film go? We watch as four friends pretend to be mobsters for easy money.  Mind you these are four high school boys who do not look like they are in school.  Is this even believable? I didn't believe this premise. It appears that the director couldn't push the characters as far as he needed to go since they were underaged. However, these actors are so mature that they couldn't bring it down to high school level. Heres a suggestion: if you want to make a teen film get teenagers. This film has the look that it was made for a  favor to a friend.

Boring, unbelievable and trite.  I graduated from high school in Reno and played sports there.  Nothing in this movie seems remotely possible, other than kids attending high school together.
